==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Plebiscite
<hw>Pleb"i*scite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pl⟦eacute⟧biscite</ets>, fr. L. <ets>plebiscitum</ets>.]</ety>
<def>A vote by universal male suffrage; especially, in France, a popular
vote, as first sanctioned by the National Constitution of 1791.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>plebiscit</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Plebiscite</qex> we have lately taken, in popular use, from
the French.</q> <rj><qau>Fitzed. Hall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plebiscitum</ent>⟦br⟧
